sentences: John William Fedchock (born September 18, 1957) is an American jazz trombonist, bandleader, and arranger.
Fedchock was born in Cleveland, Ohio.
Fedchock worked for the Woody Herman Orchestra in the 1980s and was noted for his arrangements.
He recorded his first album as a leader in 1992 with the New York Big Band, which was active into the late-2000s.
